19/04/2005
NEW YORK, United States -- The UN, the EU and the United States issued separate statements Monday (18 April) hailing the election of pro-unity Turkish Cypriot leader Mehmet Ali Talat as president of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus (TRNC). 
Talat, the incumbent TRNC prime minister, won the election the previous day and will succeed Rauf Denktash. 
According to the international community, the choice by voters signals a commitment to the peaceful resolution of the Cyprus issue. 
(Kathimerini - 19/04/05; UN, Council of Europe Web sites, NTV - 18/04/05)
